   </svg>
  </copy-clipboard>
 </i18n-message></h3>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p>Version control repository (e.g., GitLab repository) with the Maven and Node.js projects.</p>
 </li>
 <li>
  <p>Basic knowledge of Maven and Node.js build tools.</p>
 </li>
 <li>
  <p>Access to a GitLab CI/CD platform (can be self-hosted or cloud-based).</p>
 </li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Step-1:-Set-Up-GitLab-CI/CD-Configuration-(Create-.gitlab-ci.yml-File):"><span id="ContinuousIntegration(CI)JobsforMavenandNode.jsProjects-Step1:SetUpGitLabCI/CDConfiguration(Create.gitlab-ci.ymlFile):"></span>Step 1: Set Up GitLab CI/CD Configuration (Create .gitlab-ci.yml File):&nbsp;
 <i18n-message i18nkey="clipboard.copyLink.label" attribute="description">
  <copy-clipboard class="anchor-copy-button" value="https://docs.expertflow.com/cx/4.3/continuous-integration-ci-jobs-for-maven-and-node-#Step-1:-Set-Up-GitLab-CI/CD-Configuration-(Create-.gitlab-ci.yml-File):">
   <svg role="img" aria-hidden="true" data-component="icon" class="icon icon-link copy-headline-link-icon">
    <use href="/__theme/b_8ca5a7d7-80f3-41c8-bea7-75cce14ad14f/scroll-sites-help-center-theme/41/icons.svg#link"></use>
   </svg>
  </copy-clipboard>
 </i18n-message></h2>
<p><span style="--color: #374151">The </span><code>.gitlab-ci.yml</code><span style="--color: #374151"> file is a configuration file used by GitLab CI/CD to define the CI/CD pipeline for your project. It is written in YAML format and is typically placed in the root directory of your GitLab repository. The file defines the stages, jobs, and scripts to execute for each job. </span></p>
<ol>
 <li>
  <p>Create a file named .gitlab-ci.yml in the root directory of your Maven and Node.js projects.</p>
 </li>
 <li>
  <p>Open the .gitlab-ci.yml file and define the CI/CD pipeline stages and jobs.</p>
 </li>
 <li>
  <p>For Java projects, you can copy the <code>.gitlab-ci.yaml</code> file from the Conversation Manager as a template and update maven version.</p>
 </li>
 <li>
  <p>For Node.js projects, you can copy the <code>.gitlab-ci.yaml</code> file from the Agent Manager as a template and update Node.js version.</p>
 </li>
</ol>
<h2 id="Step-2:-Configuring-Maven-and-Node.js-Projects:"><span id="ContinuousIntegration(CI)JobsforMavenandNode.jsProjects-Step2:ConfiguringMavenandNode.jsProjects:"></span>Step 2: Configuring Maven and Node.js Projects:
